This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for fitting flexible variational posteriors in Bayesian neural networks. The paper also includes experiments on regression and classification tasks, which are common in the field of machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as Bayesian neural networks are a popular topic in AI research. 

The paper's focus on classification tasks suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision), as classification is a common task in computer vision. 

The use of natural gradient optimization and matrix factorization techniques suggests it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control), as these fields often use these techniques in their research. 

Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SY.
